# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

## 2.3.0 (2026-03-10)

### Added

- Support for 8 task list states: `[ ]`, `[x]`, `[~]`, `[@]`, `[-]`, `[!]`, `[>]`, `[?]`
- WikiLink syntax with aliases: `[[Page|Display Text]]`
- Foldable admonitions with `-` modifier

### Changed

- Math blocks now use `$$` delimiters exclusively
- Table parser handles uneven column counts gracefully

### Fixed

- Inline code spans with backtick escaping
- Footnote definitions with multi-line content
- Empty heading content no longer causes a panic

## 2.2.0 (2026-02-15)

### Added

- Front matter parsing (YAML between `---` fences)
- Definition lists with `: ` prefix
- `[TOC]` directive with optional level range

### Changed

- Improved paragraph continuation logic
- Better error messages for unclosed fences

### Deprecated

- The `\(` math delimiter is no longer supported (use `$` instead)

## 2.1.0 (2026-01-20)

### Added

- Admonition blocks: `N>`, `T>`, `W>`, `!>`, `X>`
- Fenced divs with `:::` syntax
- Superscript and subscript support

### Fixed

- Link parsing with nested brackets
- Blockquote continuation across blank lines
